Exploratory Data Analysis - Capstone project(Module - Basic Data Science)¶

Perform exploratory data analysis on the given dataset using Python, Numpy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn.¶

Add Python comments to explain your code.¶

For each of the five sections given below, mention conclusions/observations drawn by you after code implementation.¶

1. Data pre-processing (10 marks)¶

a. Analyse data types of features¶

b. Identify dependent and independent features¶

c. Check for null values data and remove if any with appropriate method¶

2. Univariate analysis (20 marks)¶

a. Remove outliers¶

b. Categorical features: countplot, numeric features: histogram¶

c. Identify skewed features¶

3. Bivariate analysis (20 marks)¶

a. using correlation with heatmap¶

b. scatter plot with hue parameter¶

c. pair plot¶

4. Feature engineering (5 marks)¶

a. Convert categorical features into numeric one using appropriate encoding techniques.¶

5. In addition to above mentioned methods, you are allowed to use any other EDA method. (5 marks)¶

Note –¶

1. The comments and conclusions/observations carry marks for each section.¶

2. Students should submit their work in the form of .ipynb code file to Dr. Nilay (nilayk@regenesys.net) and Hetal (hetalg@regenesys.net).¶

3. Please following the filename format as below: Name_of_student-Batch_name-Capstone_project_1.ipynb.¶

4. Keep same naming convention as mentioned above for the subject of email.¶

5. Duration of the project work is set to one month from the date of project work announcement. Last date of submission is 30th September 2022.¶
